div1.p:
Q. Whose boxes were these (to
Susannah Miles
). A. One belonged to me and one to my brother.

Q.(to
Susannah Miles
) Is that your silk cloak. - A. Yes, I am sure of it.

Q.(to
Susannah Miles
) Is that a black silk cloak. A. Yes.

Q.(to
George Page
) Look at that handkerchief, that was found on the person of Daley, are you sure that that was one of the handkerchiefs that you shewed them. - A. I am positive that I had such a handkerchief in the box.

Q. Did you mention any thing about the person that has been mentioned. - A. The clerk of the check having stated in the first instance to me that he believed him to be an imposter;
John Neason
's name was mentioned in the board to him by me, he told me that his brother had been a sergeant, that he believed at the time the capture was made he was a corporal; I asked him what became of his brother, he told me that he heard that he died in the West Indies.
